data.name: Chilled Beet Soup
data.quickTastyDescription: A refreshing chilled soup packed with vibrant beets and fresh vegetables, perfect for hot days.
detailedCookingInstructions: In a large bowl, combine cooked and diced beets, diced cucumber, sliced radishes, and chopped green onion.
In a separate bowl, mix the plain yogurt (or sour cream), vegetable broth, lemon juice, and chopped dill until smooth.
Pour the yogurt mixture over the beet and vegetable mixture, stirring gently to combine.
Chill in the refrigerator for at least 30 minutes before serving to enhance the flavors.
Serve cold, garnished with additional dill if desired.
data.modifiersForBase: Chilled and served cold with fresh vegetables
